<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
The information about the water/flood damage makes total sense!  
<br />

<br />
When I went up to the Bowling Green area last summer, it seemed like every cemetery we visited was on a small hill.  It's pretty flat up there, definitely a lot less hills than we have down here.  
<br />

<br />
The only downside I can see to having cemeteries located on hills, especially steep ones, is erosion.  Sometimes the graves located on the slope of these hills have almost all the ground beneath them eroded away...it looks like the stones could just fall over.</td>
